Rating: 3
I agree, this crust is to die for. But I found it dry, and hesitated to use more liquid or suffer the consequences of a tought dough. My pears were not ripe enough, so they didn't produce enough juice. I followed other's suggestion and put the chocolate on the bottom, not enough for me! I will add it on top as well next time.

Rating: 2
Made for Thanksgiving to showcase some local goodies. The crust was so easy and came out great, although I received my annual hand injury when the brand new food processor blade sliced BENEATH my fingernail and up through the nail. Lovely. But overall, the tart was a bit lackluster, not quite what I was expecting. Something tasted stale about it like the flavors didn't quite fit, and I didn't feel the pears stood up to the chocolate very well, even though I love pairing pears with chocolate. Would I make again...???

