I wasn't too crazy about this dish. If I were to do this again, I'd use only the semi-sweet chocolate and put the chocolate on the bottom. The milk cholocate tasted flat and funny in comparesin to the semi-sweet and how it melted on the top rather than the bottom make for an unattractive presentation. The crust was fantastic though!

Rating: 4
Fantastic and so simple. My only change was to use 2/3rd of a chopped cadbury dark chocolate and 2/3rds of a chopped milk chocolate bar (chocolate lovers in the house). We omitted the sugar but kept the salt. Delish.

