This recipe was a big hit at the dinner party I had last night. The combination of pears, hazelnuts and chocolate is wonderful.

Rating: 4
This was really easy and really good. The crust was easy to work with. I traced a 14" circle in pencil on the reverse of the parchment to make sure I rolled it out enough. Guests really liked it.

Rating: 4
A truly outstanding recipe. The combination of the pears, chocolate and hazelnut is superb. I could only use 2-3 of the pears on my tart; maybe I didn't roll out the crust out thin enough. I found the dough a little stiff to work with (maybe needed more cream or ice water) but the texture and taste of the tart crust superior. I also used half the amount of raw sugar called for and it was plenty. Do add the small sprinkling of sea salt before baking; it adds a subtle and surprising difference in flavor.